cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CR

The paper discusses a variant of the h-index that considers only recent publications, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with bibliometrics and citation analysis. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as it deals with measuring the impact of scientific publications. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible categories as they deal with analyzing and predicting scientific performance. Finally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but it could be relevant if the paper discusses the security of the ISI Web of Knowledge.
